args: Heeeeey, Rena! I just found a wooden box\nin the storeroom—any idea what it is?
Oh, right! I found that in the attic\nwhen we first moved into the castle.
Hey, I remember that! We were in such\na hurry to get settled, we never checked\nto see what was inside.
I wanna knoooow! ...Can we open it?
Well, I don't see why not.\nLet me grab my blade and—
You're still on blade ban, missy!\nI'll just open it like a normal person.
*cough* *hack* Blech! There's dust\neverywhere! You should've opened it\nmore slowly.
*wheeeeze* Yeah, maybe I used\na bit too much force there...
Guess we should crack this puppy\nopen too, huh? Lemme just...
Oh hey, it's a sword!\n...But a real crappy one.
Rena, am I seein' things,\nor is this Dad's mark?
Whaaat?! How in the hey did DAD\nforge a piece of junk like this?!

I'm guessin' it was one of his rare failures.
See how the blade is distorted? That's
what happens when your forge ain't the
right temperature.
I imagine it was either an experiment\ngone wrong or just a youthful mistake.
I'm guessin' he mixed somethin' into\nthe steel based on the weight.
...What would you two say\nto us tryin' to reforge this?
I don't think finishin' it would take\ntoo much effort on our part.
We can't just take a sword he obviously\ndidn't intend people to find and mess\naround with it like a bunch of...messers!
Actually, I think he'd be happy if we made\nsomethin' good from one of his failures.
Failure or not, it's a memento of him,\nand we should leave it alone!
Now, now... There's no need to fight.
Dad wouldn't want some failure to be\nfloatin' around in the world—he'd want\nus to fix it and avenge his good name!
No! We should display it just as it is!
Ramona? Renee?\nLet's all take a breath.
Let's take this one step at a time.\nEach of you tell me what you want to do.
It's one of Dad's works—I want us to\nkeep it around to remember him by.
And if I was him, I wouldn't want some\nunfinished work dirtyin' my name.\nWe should reforge it.
I can see the logic in both points.
And while I also want to preserve Dad's\nmemory, I don't know how happy he'd\nbe to have this sword in the public eye.
But I think I have an idea that will\nmake everyone happy.
How? I mean, we can't do both.
Oh, you just leave it to me...
Now both of you, please do everything\nexactly like I just taught you.
Ancient sword, awaken from\nyour slumber with a shine!
Be reborn in light before us!
We pour our hearts into you!
The light is...soft. It's like it's wrapped\nitself around the sword somehow.
It reminds me of Mom and Dad.
Yes, well, I think this is MUCH improved.\nWe should display it in the shop.
That way, we won't forget Dad OR the fact\nthat everyone has to start somewhere.
I guess Dad was makin' nothin' but\nmasterpieces at the end, huh?
People used to say his swords could \ncleave the waves and his hammers\ncould ＂rend the earth in twain.＂
But way back in the day, he cranked out\nshoddy duds like this sword here.
So do you think we're younger now\nthan he was when he made this?
So if we try really hard, we might be\nable to become even BETTER than him!
Maybe—but we'll really have to work at it.
Great! In that case, I'm gonna start\nby being better than the two of you!
I want you both to remember Dad\nwhenever you look at this sword.
Remember how he always strove\nto improve, never forgot his roots,\nand eventually became a legend.
I'll do more than that—I'll think about\nwhat he thought whenever HE looked at it.
Hee hee! Probably something like,\n＂I'll be damned if I ever make a\npiece of junk like YOU again!＂
Those humble feelings are what make\nthis sword shine!
